Jeff Wicks, News24(ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - The death toll from a mass casualty bus accident in Chatsworth on Monday has risen to three. Medics at the scene have transported the injured to hospitals across the city and are now searching the wreckage. It is understood that three people died within the bus. Key sources say that the toll may rise as the search beneath the wreckage continues.- Are you there? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos. Earlier, paramedics reported that the accident on the M1 Higginson Highway near Savannah Park in Chatsworth had left two people dead and at least 70 injured.KZN EMS spokesperson Robert McKenzie said that initial reports from the scene indicate that four people had been critically injured.He said that the Red Cross Air Mercy Helicopter as well as a SANDF 15 Squadron Oryx had been activated to assist with airlifting the critically injured to hospital.RescueCare spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said that medics on the ground faced a frenetic scene and had called for ambulances from across the city to aid at the crash site. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.